oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Boyer family in front of home on Pigeon River
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: F. Boyer, Ann Dennis Weaver Boyer and their family in front of their home on Pigeon River. A baby carriage is also pictured.
Boyer was sheriff of Cocke County for five terms. He served in the State Legislature as a Republican.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Dwellings; Families; Dogs; Baby carriages
